dct_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Morpeth, drift, sheet 14
dct_description_sm: Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. Geological Survey of Great Britain (England and Wales). Sheet 14 drift. Geological Survey of Great Britain. North Decimal Degree 55.166700. South Decimal Degree 55.0000. East Decimal Degree -1.5833. West Decimal Degree -2.0167. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of Great Britain. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Published (as Sheet 105 N.W. Old Series) in 1892. Resurveyed in 1922-1937 by W. Anderson, G. A. Burnett, V.A. Eyles, A. Fowler, J. Maden, and R.G. Carruthers (District Geologist).".
